        <briefdescription>
<para>Functions for interrupts, in <ref refid="xiicps__intr_8c" kindref="compound">xiicps_intr.c</ref>. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Sets the status callback function, the status handler, which the driver calls when it encounter conditions that should be reported to the higher layer software.</para><para>The handler executes in an interrupt context, so the amount of processing should be minimized.</para><para>Refer to the <ref refid="xiicps_8h" kindref="compound">xiicps.h</ref> file for a list of the Callback events. The events are defined to start with XIICPS_EVENT_*.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_iic_ps" kindref="compound">XIicPs</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>CallBackRef</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Upper layer callback reference passed back when the callback function is invoked. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>FunctionPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the callback function.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
The handler is called within interrupt context, so it should finish its work quickly. </para>        </detaileddescription>
